# Arduino sketches

## Arduino IDE constraint

The sketch folder name **must match** the `.ino` filename (without extension).

```
projects/03-sensor-read/
  03-sensor-read.ino   ✅
  sensor-read.ino      ❌
```

## Structure

- Use standard `setup()` and `loop()`.
- When a sketch grows beyond ~100 lines, extract reusable logic into `.h` / `.cpp` files in the same folder.

## Documentation

- Document all pin assignments and peripherals in `docs/wiring.md`.
- List board model and components in `docs/hardware.md`.

## Arduino Uno defaults

- 16 MHz, 5 V logic
- ~2 KB SRAM — avoid large buffers and long strings; mention memory impact when relevant
- Built-in LED: `LED_BUILTIN` (pin 13)

## Timing

- `delay()` is fine for simple sketches (e.g. blink).
- For multitasking (sensors + motors + comms), prefer non-blocking patterns (`millis()` timers) — note this in docs when introducing it.

## Libraries

- Prefer built-in Arduino libraries when possible.
- Vendored copies go in the project's `lib/` folder; document the library and version in `docs/hardware.md`.
